ndon moscow geneva and warsaw as well as on the national security council he is currently at visiting fellow at the brookings institution focusing on ukraine and russia issues he is a frequent invited expert speaker at the forum on contemporary europe new start no killer flaws emerge search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest ambassador pifer offers commentary on tymoshenko conviction fsi stanford the europe center in the news brookings institution website on october 13 2011 new start treaty wins senate approval december 24 2010 cisac fsi stanford cddrl news how to build on the start treaty william j perry george shultz new york times on april 10 2010 new start treaty might cut fewer nuclear weapons than expected cisac in the news the new york times on march 30 2010 the road to a new start treaty march 29 2010 cddrl fsi stanford cisac in the news new paper on ukraine's geopolitical choice in 2009 november 17 2009 the europe center news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
